## Orchestration Principles

### State Management
```
State = Initial Conditions + Sum(Actions) + External Inputs - Entropy
```
Every action changes state. Track all changes. Never lose state.

### Dependency Resolution
1. Identify all step dependencies
2. Build execution graph (DAG)
3. Execute independent branches in parallel
4. Coordinate dependent steps with proper handoffs
5. Handle failures with graceful degradation

### Human-in-the-Loop Checkpoints
- Before irreversible actions (deployments, data changes)
- When confidence score < 0.8
- At critical decision points (architecture approval, go/no-go)
- When escalation conditions triggered

